{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ef665328-74d8-46c7-9ab1-eea90494e692","content":"Two things changed with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changed\n\nWith MTP, `dotnet test` uses **MSTest filter syntax** where `&` becomes `/` (for AND):\n\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests/Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n| v2 (VSTest) | v3 (MTP) |\n|---|---|\n| `&` (AND) | `/` |\n| `\\|` (OR) | `\\|` (same) |\n| `!` (NOT) | `!` (same) |\n\n### 2. `[Trait]` → `[Category]` attribute\n\nxUnit v3 dropped `[Trait(\"Category\", ...)]` and added a first-class `[Category]` attribute. Your filter matches `Category=Smoke`, so update the test:\n\n```csharp\n// Before (v2):  [Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]\n// After  (v3):  [Category(\"Smoke\")]\n```\n\n### Updated CI command\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests/Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nWant me to apply the `[Trait]` → `[Category]` change to your test file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1b522c30-2f2e-4532-8dff-738d84feab2c","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"E3C0:AB6AD:1C6BBBB:1F66A6F:6A0520A4"},"id":"e723d23d-3ef4-4b59-8208-7e34404cd83c","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:08:59.350Z","parentId":"d23b000f-e5f4-4035-8924-0107d66565e3"}
